---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Educational Philosophy">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-8 relative">
    <div class="absolute -left-12 top-0 bottom-0 w-[1px] bg-earth/20 hidden md:block"></div>
    
    <header class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-serif text-ink tracking-tight mb-6">Educational Philosophy</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-ink-light font-serif italic border-l-2 border-clay pl-4">
        Language is not a subject to be learned; it is an environment to be inhaled.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-headings:font-serif prose-headings:text-ink prose-p:text-ink-light prose-p:leading-relaxed max-w-none">
      
      <h2>The 4E Cognitive Approach</h2>
      <p>
        My pedagogical engineering is rooted in <strong>4E Cognition</strong>. I believe that language acquisition is:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Embodied:</strong> We do not learn a language just with our brains, but with our entire sensory-motor system.</li>
        <li><strong>Embedded:</strong> Language only makes sense within a rich environmental context.</li>
        <li><strong>Enacted:</strong> We acquire language by doing things in the world, not by passively observing it.</li>
        <li><strong>Extended:</strong> Our linguistic mind extends into the tools, texts, and environments we use.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Comprehensible Input</h2>
      <p>
        I design experiences where the target language (Spanish) is so compelling and understandable that the brain cannot help but acquire it. This means moving away from grammar drills and moving towards <strong>meaningful, message-driven communication</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>The Garden Metaphor</h2>
      <p>
        Instead of a factory where students are assembled, or a laboratory where they are tested, I view the acquisition process as a <strong>botanical garden</strong>. My role is not to force the plant to grow, but to architect the ideal soil, light, and water conditions—the perfect ecosystem of comprehensible input—so that acquisition flourishes naturally.
      </p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
